N.B.
Seller NP should perform an inventory & price check in /on_init. In case of item out of stock, errorresponse should be same as in/on_select;
Seller NPmay apply buyer-specific cashback offers(can only be applied only after the buyer is identified).These offers cannot be a part of the catalog and will be explicitly applied in /on_init, with title_type = "offer" and quote.breakup[].price.value having a negative value equal to the cashback; however, the rules in the previous section for item count / value for offer will still hold;
If /on_select returned multiple fulfillment options, the buyer may switch the fulfillment option from the default fulfillment(s) assigned in /on_select. In this case, the quote in /on_init will be updated based on the fulfillment option selected by buyer;
The quote in /on_init will be the final quote for the order prior to /confirm. Both seller NP & buyer NP respectively should validate that the quote in /confirm and /on_confirm matches the quote in /on_init (both for the total and for individual line items);
