Rules for part return & cancel
An order is frozen at its terminal state ("Completed", "Cancelled"), with no further updates, except for the following:
With order.state = "Completed", there may be return of 1 or more items, within the return window for these items. For every return request, a separate fulfillment is created to track the return request and the refund associated with the return request;
Order & fulfillment state, for forward shipment fulfillment, is set to "Cancelled", whenever RTO is initiated for an order;
Changes to the order due to return / RTO are defined in the contract for the corresponding APIs;
Response for part-return should have exactly the same number of items for which return is requested;
Order value (quote.price.value) cannot increase through /on_update. If order value decreases, it should be due to decrease in item quantity (quote.breakup[]."@ondc/org/item_quantity".count) for "@ondc/org/title_type" of "item";
Quote trail is immutable after it is added to the order at the refund trigger point;
/on_update should return the same information as /on_statusi.e. the audit trail for items (including returns, cancels processed or in-progress), the current state of order items & fulfillment, order quote and breakup, settlement trail (if available);
/on_update (solicited or unsolicited) should be called whenever there is a change in the order details (e.g. due to buyer return or cancellation). Whenever there is a status change, an unsolicited /on_status call should be made;
Batching of order updates & status changes should not be done;
