Transaction level contract
Overview
Purpose of the transaction level contract  between the participating NPs is explainedhereand includes the standard terms & conditions for the network participant(s);
The codified digital contract includes a set of configurable terms defined by the seller and a set of static terms which will be defined by the buyer NP (BNP);
A reference to these static terms will be a part of every online transaction between 2 participants;
Reference clauses to serve as a guide for participants to draft their static terms for the codified digital contract can be foundhere;
Proposed flow
Static terms will be version-controlled in GitHubrepo:
All static terms will start with version 1.0.0 and subsequent changes will increment the version;
NP creates a PR for their static terms and ONDC will merge this PR and share the link with the NP:
NP forks the repository and creates a branch under the appropriate version, using the following naming convention:
<NP name>_role e.g. "Pincode_BNP", "Magicpin_BNP", etc.;
NP merges their static terms into this branch;
NP creates PR for these changes;
Static terms can be publishedby NP on multiple channels e.g. their website, ONDC portal, etc.
Communication & acceptance of static terms:
Communication by BNP
BNP sends the following additional info as part of /search:
currentstatic terms link with version:
for the very 1st set of static terms, this will be a blank link;
newstatic terms link with version, if any:
for the very 1st static terms, this will be the link for static terms in GitHub;
effective date for new static terms
Info in (i) above will be sent in /search for full catalog for 24 hrs, after this version of static terms is published;
24 hrs prior to expiry of effective date in (i) above, BNP resends additional info in (i) above;
If BNP wants to change the effective date, they can update the effective date in (i) above and repeat (ii) & (iii) above;
If BNP wants to change their static terms, they need to resubmit their PR with new version no;
It is recommended that the BNP should give at least 15 days of advance notice when they are changing their static terms.
Acceptance by seller NP (SNP)
If SNP accepts the static terms in /search above, they need to send accept="Y" in /on_search;
If SNP doesn’t accept the static terms in /search above, they need to send accept="N" in /on_search;
If SNP doesn’t accept the static terms for a BNP, they should stop responding with their catalog for the corresponding BNP from the effective date;
If SNP doesn’t accept the static terms but continues to send their catalog, BNP may, at their discretion, choose to delist the sellers for this SNP;
Static terms agreed to between the BNP & SNP will be a part of /confirm and /confirm;
Transaction flows
Buyer NP (BNP) integration with logistics
Integration between retail buyer NP (BNP) & LSP will have similar flow as for retail seller NP;
Since logistics is a separate domain, BNP needs to register as buyer NP for the logistics domain (LBNP);
Retail seller NP (SNP) that supports fulfillment by BNP will also enable the fulfillment type "Buyer-Delivery";
Integration steps are defined for pre-order flow (i.e. up to creation of logistics order) and post-order flow (i.e. status & other update, cancellation, tracking), withadditions to retail contract highlighted;
Pre-order flow
LSP catalog
connected: on-network call for LSP catalog:
LBNP sends /search thru gateway & gateway broadcasts to LSPs:
Logistics /search requires start & end gps coordinates & city code, weight / dimensions of package being shipped, etc.;
Logistics /search[1134]should be sequenced after receiving response for retail /select;
LSP(s) send logistics catalog directly to LBNP;
disconnected:
BNP maintains rate card for logistics (includes rate, TAT for distance slabs);
If SNP supports "Buyer-Delivery" fulfillment type, /on_select should have for the corresponding fulfillment:
quote with packaging charges / convenience fee, as applicable (delivery charge of 0);
O2S TAT;
weight & dimensions of package;
SNP can also include their own fulfillment types (for delivery, self-pickup):
BNP consolidates fulfillment options from LSP & SNP for buyer;
for fulfillment options from LSP, BNP will need to compute O2D as O2S + S2D (S2D will have 1st mile & last mile components and there may be an overlap between O2S & 1st mile component especially for F&B);
If buyer selects fulfillment corresponding to "Buyer-Delivery" fulfillment type, corresponding fulfillment id should be mapped to item and passed in /init to SNP:
In response, SNP will send the updated quote, for the selected fulfillment, including packaging charges / convenience fee (as applicable) & O2S TAT;
SNP also updates whether RTO action results in actual return to origin;
Order will be confirmed with SNP with the above fulfillment id / quote / TAT as sent by SNP in /on_init:
Logistics order will be confirmed by LBNP with the selected fulfillment id;
Post-order flow
State update:
SNP updates retail order state to "Packed";
SNP notifies "ready_to_ship" for retail order:
"ready_to_ship" and "Packed" may be sent in any sequence:
at the same time;
"ready_to_ship" followed by "Packed";
"Packed" followed by "ready_to_ship";
SNP also sends pickup code (PCC / authorization) along with "ready_to_ship";
On receiving "ready_to_ship" from SNP, LBNP notifies "ready_to_ship" to LSP, with pickup code:
In response, LSP updates pickup slot & shipping label (for hub-based delivery);
BNP forwards pickup slot & shipping label (for hub-based delivery) to SNP using /update;
When agent is assigned ("Agent-assigned"), LSP sends agent details to LBNP using /on_status:
BNP forwards this status to SNP using /update:
SNP will need to handle cases where fulfillment states are received out of sequence, e.g. "Agent-assigned" before "Packed";
After fulfillment is picked up, LSP updates status of logistics order to "Order-picked-up", with pickup time:
BNP requests update of retail order / fulfillment state & pickup time using /update;
After fulfillment is delivered, LSP updates state of logistics order to "Order-delivered":
BNP requests update of retail order / fulfillment state & delivery time using /update;
After all fulfillments are marked "Order-delivered", SNP should update order state to "Completed";
All interim states between iv & vi will also be updated in same way;
In case of off-network logistics, all state updates need to be provided by BNP in same way;
Cancellation:
LSP cancels:
LSP cancels logistics order using /on_cancel, withreason codeand their subscriber id in "cancelled_by";
BNP cancels the retail order / fulfillment (passing the same cancellation reason from LSP);
If RTO initiated:
BNP requests state update, for forward & reverse fulfillment, for retail order(see "State update" above);
SNP may cancel order either at "RTO_Initiated" or terminal state ("RTO_Delivered", "RTO_Disposed");
Cancellation charges (including RTO costs as applicable) will be communicated by BNP to SNP, if SNP is liable for such charges:
state update & cancellation charges will be communicated to SNP using /update;
cancellation charges will not be included in the order quote and separate keys will be provided for this (as these are receivables due from SNP to BNP);
Buyer / BNP cancels:
BNP cancels retail order / fulfillment using /cancel;
BNP cancels logistics order using /cancel;
If RTO initiated:
BNP requests state update, for forward & reverse fulfillment, for retail order(see "State updates" above);
SNP to cancel order either at RTO initiation or terminal state;
Cancellation charges including RTO costs (as applicable) will be communicated by BNP to SNP, if SNP is liable for such charges:
state update & cancellation charges will be communicated to SNP using /update;
cancellation charges will not be included in the order quote and separate keys will be provided for this (as these are receivables due from SNP to BNP);
SNP cancels:
SNP cancels retail order / fulfillment using /on_cancel;
BNP cancels logistics order (passing same cancellation reason from SNP) using /cancel;
If RTO initiated:
BNP request state update, for forward & reverse fulfillment, for retail order(see "Status updates" above);
SNP to cancel order either at RTO initiation or terminal state;
Cancellation charges including RTO costs (as applicable) will be communicated by BNP to SNP, if SNP is liable for such charges:
state update & cancellation charges will be communicated to SNP using /update;
cancellation charges will not be included in the order quote and separate keys will be provided for this (as these are receivables due from SNP to BNP);
For off-network logistics, all state updates for forward / reverse fulfillment need to be provided by BNP;
Return:
Charges:
SNP handles return pickup => no additional charges to be sent in order quote;
SNP doesn’t handle return pickup => BNP will need to factor in return costs;
Flow:
SNP handles return pickup => existing flow applies;
SNP doesn’t handle return pickup:
BNP sends return request;
SNP approves return request with status "Return_Approved"and also sends reverse qc details for return pickup check;
BNP creates & places order for logistics for return pickup;
BNP requests state update, for return fulfillment(see "Status update" above);
Tracking:
Tracking of order / fulfillment will be directly between BNP & LSP:
SNP tracking - may be enabled later;
Other updates:
In case of part-cancel of items, BNP may update logistics order with updated weight / dimensions / order value;
Weight differential
LSP sends updated quote / weight / dimension due to weight differential to LBNP:
LBNP forwards weight / dimension / receivables due from SNP, due to weight differential, to SNP;
SNP to inform BNP if they accept or dispute the weight differential updates:
If SNP disputes:
LBNP communicates to LSP that weight differential updates are rejected;
LSP handles order delivery as per static terms;
resolution of dispute will follow IGM route (details tbd);
If SNP accepts:
differential cost will not be included in order quote and separate keys will be provided for this (as these are receivables due from SNP to BNP);
Summary of additions to retail contract
/on_search:
additional fulfillment option for provider for "Buyer-Delivery";
/on_select:
quote with packaging charges / misc for fulfillment option "Buyer-Delivery";
O2S TAT for fulfillment option "Buyer-Delivery";
weight & dimensions of package for fulfillment option "Buyer-Delivery";
/on_init:
whether (items in) fulfillment should be returned in case of RTO;
updated fulfillment TAT for O2S;
/confirm:
Confirmed retail order details will also include weight & dim for order, O2S TAT;
/update:
Order / fulfillment state updates;
Communication of receivables due from SNP to BNP;
Seller NP (SNP) collecting payment
SNP that wants to collect payment should set "bpp_terms"."collect_payment" to "Y" in /on_search (full catalog refresh);
Buyer NP (BNP) that wants to place order with this SNP will need to render the payment link sent by SNP:
SNP sends following additional attributes in /on_init for rendering payment link:
payment.type="ON-ORDER" (prepaid);
payment.collected_by="BPP";
payment.uri="secure_public_pg_link";
payment.status="NOT-PAID";
BNP will need to render this payment link for the buyer, after receiving the /on_init response;
SNP updates payment collection details using unsolicited /on_init:
Scenario 1 - collection successful, payment status updated:
payment.params:currency, amount (order value), transaction_id (unique transaction reference);
payment.status="PAID";
payment.tags.bpp_collect.success="Y";
in this case, BNP should proceed with /confirm;
Scenario 2 - collection successful, payment status not updated:
payment.params:currency, amount (order value), transaction_id (if available);
payment.status="NOT-PAID";
payment.tags.bpp_collect.success="Y";
in this case, BNP may terminate the transaction or proceed with /confirm. If BNP proceeds with /confirm, SNP should honour /confirm as per the contract and it will be the SNP’s responsibility to subsequently update payment.status when available;
Scenario 3 - collection error:
payment.params:currency, amount (order value);
payment.status="NOT-PAID";
payment.tags.bpp_collect.success="N";
payment.tags.bpp_collect.error="error_message";
in this case, BNP should terminate the transaction;
If BNP doesn’t receive payment collection details (as per 3 above) within its TAT:
BNP should terminate the transaction and if the payment collection details are subsequently received, it should NACK /on_init with error code 20009;
BNP may also send another /init request for the latest payment collection details and follow (a) above if the /on_init callback doesn’t have the required payment collection details;
Force cancellation
Considering that /cancel is a request by buyer NP (BNP) for seller NP (SNP) to cancel order / fulfillment, there may be a need for BNP to initiate "force cancellation" for certain cases like buyer requesting cancellation due to fulfillment TAT breach;
All orders / fulfillment(s) can be cancelled at any stage before delivery;
Cancellation terms can be defined by SNP:
includes cancellation fee as flat amount / % (% to be interpreted as follows):
% of order value (excluding taxes) for order cancellation;
% of fulfillment value (i.e. item + fulfillment level costs excluding taxes) for fulfillment cancellation (in case of multiple fulfillments);
for order with multiple fulfillments, cancellation fees may be defined as %;
can be optionally defined at:
order level (in /on_init);
will be applicable, for cancellation of order / fulfillment, only after corresponding order state is "Accepted";
Cancellation terms definition:
/on_init - cancellation fee for specific fulfillment state & reason code, with option for wildcard ("*") as the catch-all clause covering combination of fulfillment state & reason code not specifically defined;
Cancellation fee calculation:
for /on_cancel response:
(order value - updated order value in /on_cancel)
for no /on_cancel response:
if matching the specific fulfillment state & reason code, the cancellation fee will be as defined in cancellation terms for /on_init;
if not matching, cancellation fee will be 0;
Cancellation:
BNP initiates cancellation for order / fulfillment using /cancel (with reason code / fulfilment id, as applicable);
Includes TAT for receiving valid cancellation response;
If SNP sends valid /on_cancel response within TAT:
response has updated quote, order / fulfillment state set to cancelled;
BNP processes response and calculates cancellation fee as defined above;
If SNP doesn’t send validresponse/ doesn’t respond within TAT:
BNP sends force cancel request for order / fulfillment, i.e. /cancel request with "force" = "yes";
If SNP sends valid response within TAT, processing will be as defined in c above;
If SNP doesn’t send (valid) response:
BNP will create IGM issue for resolution (after expiry of TAT), including details such as cancellation fee calculated, refund issued (as applicable);
resolution of IGM issue will create a valid /on_cancel response for the "force" cancellation;
Authorization (OTP)
Authorization enables seller NP (SNP) to authorize pickup and logistics buyer NP (LBNP) to authorize delivery of an order on verification of specific auth code (e.g. OTP), generated for this purpose;
Proposed flow for authorization is:
SNP requests for LSP that supports authorization for pickup:
If SNP is not LBNP, this request will be routed through LBNP;
LBNP requests for LSP that supports authorization for delivery:
1 & 2 will be in the same /search request;
Only LSPs that support authorization requested should respond with their catalog;
SNP creates auth code for pickup, with validity, and sends to LSP, typically after the order is packed:
If SNP is not LBNP, this request will be routed through LBNP;
LBNP creates auth code for delivery, with validity, and sends to BNP, typically when the order is out for delivery:
If SNP is LBNP, this will be sent using /on_status;
After the order is picked up, LSP sends /on_status with fulfillment state "Order-picked-up" and with the pickup auth code:
If BNP is LBNP, this request will be routed to SNP using /update;
SNP verifies the pickup auth code and if not valid:
NACKs request with error code 40010 (expired auth code) or 40011 (invalid auth code) which needs to be mapped by LBNP to error codes 62510 & 62511 respectively;
In case of expired auth code, seller NP subsequently regenerates auth code for pickup and sends to LSP thru LBNP;
After the order is delivered, LSP sends /on_status with fulfillment state "Order-delivered" and with delivery auth code:
LBNP verifies the delivery auth code and NACKs /on_status with error code 62510 (expired auth code) or 62511 (invalid auth code);
In case of expired auth code (error code 62510), LBNP regenerates auth code for delivery and sends to BNP:
If SNP is LBNP, this will be sent using /on_status;
